Installation
To install the Formula1 App, follow these steps:

Download the App:

Obtain the app package from Splunkbase or your preferred source.
Install the App:

Navigate to your Splunk instance.
Go to Apps > Manage Apps.
Click on Install app from file.
Upload the downloaded package and click Upload.
Restart Splunk:

After installation, restart your Splunk instance to complete the setup.
Features
Team Analytics
Performance Metrics: Track team performance over seasons with detailed metrics.
Driver Statistics: Analyze individual driver statistics such as lap times and pole positions.
Season Overviews: View season-by-season breakdowns of team performance.
Hall of Fame
Champion Profiles: Access comprehensive profiles of all Formula 1 world champions.
Historical Data: Explore historical data of past seasons.
Achievements & Records: Discover records set by champions and compare current drivers.
Interactive Dashboards
Customizable Views: Customize dashboards to focus on specific teams, seasons, or drivers.
Real-Time Updates: Stay updated with the latest data and statistics.
Visual Insights: Use visualizations to understand trends and performance patterns.
Usage

Accessing the App:

Open your Splunk instance.
Navigate to Apps and select Formula1 App.
Navigating the Interface:

Use the navigation bar to explore different sections: Team Analytics and Hall of Fame.
Customize your dashboard views to suit your preferences.

Viewing Data:

Select specific teams, drivers, or seasons to view detailed analytical data.
Use filters and search functionalities to narrow down your data view.

Support
For support and assistance, please refer to the following resources:

Documentation: Detailed documentation is available within the app.
Community Forums: Join the Splunk community forums to ask questions and share insights.
